The paper is about automatic speech recognition (ASR) using the transformer model, which is a popular architecture in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with real-time or streaming ASR, which involves processing speech in real-time as it is spoken, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes a new architecture for the transformer model, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
